        "subject": "LU-224 Move fail_loc handling from lustre to libcfs",
        "message": "LU-224 Move fail_loc handling from lustre to libcfs\n\nThis patch goal is to move the fail_loc handling from lustre to libcfs. The\nreason being is that currently you can only do fault testing in the lustre core\ncode. By moving this code to libcfs all sub systems will be able to inject\nfaults into the system for testing purposes. This is in particular needed to\nsupport the cray gemini klnd driver since one can inject faults for testing\nfailure conditions.\n\nChange-Id: I6cd06fb36d40f99d086f48f9fdc5a183372a8be3\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
